review_blob: On tap at yellow brick pizza. 16 oz. Brett Pour for $2.50? Unbelievable! Pours a beautiful, hazy burnt orange. Two finger head that lingers to light lacing. Aroma of barnyard funk, spice and citrus. Flavors of pine resin, hay, orange rind and ball sweat. Lingering bitter finish with moderate alcohol. Just like mixing my 3 favorite beer styles. Take one third west coast ipa, add one third session ale and finish with one third sour. Would give another go
